SectionBody.Text: As used in ss. 655.93-655.94, the term:

Subsection.Text: “Lessee” means a person who contracts with a lessor for the use of a safe-deposit box.
“Lessor” means a financial institution that rents safe-deposit facilities.

“Safe-deposit box” means a safe-deposit box, vault, or other safe-deposit receptacle maintained by a lessor, and the rules relating thereto apply to property or documents kept in safekeeping in the financial institution’s vault.
